</ol>
</ol>
Test-case wm/drag_to_maximize
<ol>
<li title="action">Open an application</li>
<li title="action">Drag the title bar to the top unity panel</li>
<ol>
<li title="expected_result">A maximize preview shows, covering the whole screen</li>
</ol>
<li title="action">Release mouse button</li>
<ol>
<li title="expected_result">Window is maximized</li>
</ol>
<li title="action">Drag the title bar from the unity panel downwards</li>
<ol>
<li title="expected_result">Window is restored</li>
</ol>
<li title="action">Drag the title bar to the left so that the mouse cursor is on the left edge of the screen</li>
<ol>
<li title="expected_result">A maximize preview shows, covering the left-half of the screen</li>
</ol>
<li title="action">Release mouse button</li>
<ol>
<li title="expected_result">Window is semi-maximized to the left of the screen</li>
</ol>
<li title="action">Drag the title bar to the right so that the mouse cursor is on the right edge of the screen</li>
<ol>
<li title="expected_result">A maximize preview shows, covering the right-half of the screen</li>
</ol>
<li title="action">Release mouse button</li>
<ol>
<li title="expected_result">Window is semi-maximized to the right of the screen</li>
</ol>
</ol>
